00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,000
So let's write that.

555
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:55,000
Plus V of rho.

556
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:59,000
That also corresponds, well, okay,

557
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,000
V of rho.

558
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,000
Let's take, actually,

559
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,500
potential always comes in with

560
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:06,000
a minus sign in the Lagrangian,

561
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:09,000
so let's put it in with a minus sign.

562
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:12,000
A simple case would be rho squared,

563
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:14,000
an energy which increases

564
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,000
quadratically away from the origin.

565
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:18,000
That's a possibility.

566
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:20,000
Let's think about that possibility.

567
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:22,000
Rho squared.

568
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,000
It's not really what I,

569
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:26,000
it's a possible expression.

570
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,000
What would that correspond to?

571
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,000
What would that correspond to in

572
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:32,000
terms of phi real and phi imaginary?

573
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,000
Just rho squared.

574
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:40,000
It's phi real squared plus phi imaginary squared.

575
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:43,000
That's the Pythagorean theorem.

576
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:47,000
Rho squared is phi real squared plus phi imaginary squared.

577
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:49,000
So if the potential was

578
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:51,000
the very simple form of quadratic,

579
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:54,000
we would add here phi real squared,

580
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:56,000
or minus subtract, not important,

581
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,000
phi real squared,

582
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:01,000
plus phi imaginary squared.

583
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,000
Notice the Lagrangian would actually

584
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,000
be the sum of two terms,

585
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:11,000
one for phi real and one for phi imaginary,

586
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,000
and both of them would have a mass term.

587
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:15,000
There could be a coefficient here,

588
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:18,000
m squared over two, let's say.

589
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,500
Then you would have this

590
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:21,000
situation which I drew over here,

591
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:26,000
where both directions of oscillation correspond to a mass.

592
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:28,000
And they're quite independent of each other.

593
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,000
They don't even couple to each other.

594
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,000
They don't even talk to each other.

595
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:33,000
Just two separate fields,

596
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,000
one that I labeled phi real,

597
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:36,000
the other one I labeled phi imaginary.

598
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,500
Now there could be more complicated

599
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:39,000
things here which would couple them together,

600
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:41,500
but this is the basic picture

601
00:26:41,500 --> 00:26:44,000
if the potential looks like this.

602
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:47,000
But what if the potential looks like this?

603
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:51,000
That's also a function of rho,

604
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:53,500
