00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:32,000
that would be equivalent to ignoring H here.

668
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:35,000
Just saying rho is equal to f

669
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:36,500
plus something that takes too much

670
00:29:36,500 --> 00:29:38,000
energy for us to worry about today.

671
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,000
We'll worry about it another day

672
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:42,000
when our accelerators have more energy.

673
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:43,000
Okay?

674
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,000
What would this look like then?

675
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,000
Well,

676
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:48,000
rho is stuck at f.

677
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:51,000
We might as well ignore its derivative.

678
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,000
Okay?

679
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:54,000
Furthermore, what about V of rho?

680
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:58,000
V of rho is just V of f.

681
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:01,000
So, V is stuck at the minimum.

682
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,000
If it's stuck at the minimum,

683
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:06,000
it doesn't vary from place to place.

684
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:08,000
This and this

685
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,000
are irrelevant

686
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:14,000
to the dynamics of the angular field.

687
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,000
Furthermore,

